## SAT directories
* Depending on where the test needs to be run from there should be SAT directory on both: 
    * the admin node under `/root/hpe/SAT/` and
    * on a shared file system under `<MOUNTPOINT>/hpe/SAT/`


* Example directory layout
```
SAT
├── HPCM
│   └── h-01
│       ├── logs
│       ├── readme.md
│       ├── run.sh
│       └── runscreen.sh
├── IOBechmarks
├── PerfBenchmarks
├── Security
└── Storage
```

* Example `readme.md`
```
# test-id : brief-description

## Requirement
Full description from test plan
Est. Runtime:

## Acceptance Criteria

## Method
Logical overview of test process

## Prerequisites

## Run
</path/to/run_script>

## Results
</path/to/results>

How to interpret results
```

* Example `runscreen.sh`
```bash
date=$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M)
screen -S test-<TEST_ID> -L -Logfile logs/<TEST_ID>-${date} bash -c './run.sh'
```
